Detailed Description

cvmx_gmx::_rx::_jabber

GMX_RX_JABBER = The max size packet after which GMX will truncate

Notes: CNT must be 8-byte aligned such that CNT[2:0] == 0

The packet that will be sent to the packet input logic will have an additionl 8 bytes if GMX_RX_FRM_CTL[PRE_CHK] is set and GMX_RX_FRM_CTL[PRE_STRP] is clear. The max packet that will be sent is defined as...

max_sized_packet = GMX_RX_JABBER[CNT]+((GMX_RX_FRM_CTL[PRE_CHK] & !GMX_RX_FRM_CTL[PRE_STRP])*8)

In XAUI mode prt0 is used for checking.
